<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5880] Move java.sql.Wrapper implementations to base classes in embedded driver</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5880</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Now that the JDBC 3.0 classes in the embedded driver are compiled with source level 1.5, we could move the unwrap()/isWrapperFor() methods to the base classes to enable reuse, like we did for the client driver in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5868&quot; title=&quot;Move java.sql.Wrapper implementations to base classes on the client&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-5868&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-5868&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
